This is the quick version of how to compile and install the x10 drivers.

Step 1: Build the daemons, utilities, and device modules.  You can do 
	this as a user or as root by typing "make" in the source directory.

Step 2: Install the daemons, utilities, and device modules as root by 
	typing "make install"

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
To load the kernel module:

type "modprobe x10"

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
To run the userspace drivers:

load the driver that is associated with your device.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Follow the directions in the file html/index.html to test the drivers.
